12/09/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A two-week joint military drill of Macedonian soldiers and US troops from the Vermont National Guard began on Tuesday (12 September) at the Krivilak military ground in Macedonia. 
Soldiers will exchange experiences regarding participation in peacekeeping missions in Iraq and Afghanistan, providing practical training for the Macedonian Army in the process of NATO integration.
In other news Monday, a German military delegation arrived in Skopje for a two-day assessment of progress made in efforts to transform the Macedonian Army, particularly in forming a special operations unit. 
(Dnevnik -12/09/06; Makfax - 11/09/06)
